Package: pisR
Type: Package
Title: Useful functions for Prescribing Information System (PIS) data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Richard Papworth
Maintainer: David Henderson <d.henderson.2@research.gla.ac.uk>
Description: A suite of functions that may be frequently used when using PIS data in a safe haven environment.    
    `count_bnf_class()` summarises the number of prescriptions at at a specific level of the BNF.    
    `ever-used()` Report whether a drug appears between a defines start and end date.    
    `polypharmacy` constructs an index of polypharmacy. 
License: tbc probs CC0 or MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: tidyverse,
    stringr
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
